<法規內容>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 1</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[This standard is prescribed in accordance with the provisions of Article 17 of the Act Governing Food Sanitation.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 2</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The tolerance of aflatoxin in foods shall meet the following standards:
┌──────────┬───────────────────┐
│Food Category       │Tolerance of Total Aflatoxin          │
│                    │(Including Aflatoxin B1, B2, G1, G2)  │
├──────────┼───────────────────┤
│Peanut, corn        │Not more than 15 ppb                  │
├──────────┼───────────────────┤
│Rice, sorghum,      │Not more than 10ppb                   │
│legumes, nuts,      │                                      │
│wheat, barley and   │                                      │
│oat                 │                                      │
├──────────┼───────────────────┤
│Edible oils and fats│Not more than 10ppb                   │
├──────────┼───────────────────┤
│Milk                │Not more than 0.5 ppb (as aflatoxinM1)│
├──────────┼───────────────────┤
│Milk powder         │Not more than 5.0 ppb (as aflatoxinM1)│
├──────────┼───────────────────┤
│Other foods         │Not more than10ppb                    │
└──────────┴───────────────────┘]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 3</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The tolerance of ochratoxin A in foods shall meet the following standards:
┌──────────┬───────────────────┐
│Food Category       │Tolerance ofOchratoxin A              │
├──────────┼───────────────────┤
│Rice, wheat, barley │Not more than5ppb                     │
│and oat             │                                      │
├──────────┼───────────────────┤
│Roasted coffee beans│Not more than 5 ppb                   │
│and coffee powder   │                                      │
└──────────┴───────────────────┘]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 4</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The tolerance of patulin in foods shall meet the following standards:
┌──────────┬───────────────────┐
│Food Category       │Tolerance ofPatulin                   │
├──────────┼───────────────────┤
│Apple juice andmixed│Not more than50ppb                    │
│beverages           │                                      │
│containingapple     │                                      │
│juice               │                                      │
└──────────┴───────────────────┘]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 5</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The tolerance of citrinin in foods shall meet the following standards:
┌──────────┬───────────────────┐
│Food Category       │Tolerance ofCitrinin                  │
├──────────┼───────────────────┤
│Monascuscolor       │Not more than200ppb                   │
├──────────┼───────────────────┤
│Red yeast rice      │Not more than5 ppm                    │
├──────────┼───────────────────┤
│Complex food        │Not more than2 ppm                    │
│containingred yeast │                                      │
│rice                │                                      │
└──────────┴───────────────────┘]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 6</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The tolerance of mycotoxin in infant foods shall be compatible with the "Sanitation Standard for Infant Foods".]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 7</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[This Standard shall be implemented from the date of promulgation.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
</法規內容>
</法規>
